        <briefdescription>
<para>Spawns and configures a GameObject. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Called by the spawn system when a GameObject is acquired from a pool and needs to be initialized for gameplay. The implementation should configure the object&apos;s position, direction, and any other spawn-specific state.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gameWorld</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the current GameWorld. May be nullptr. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>level</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the current Level containing bounds and spawn info. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>gameObject</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the GameObject being spawned. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>updateContext</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The current frame&apos;s update context.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>True if spawning was successful and the object should remain active. False if spawning failed and the object should be returned to the pool. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
